## 🎯 Objectives

### Project Objectives & Outcomes
* **PCB Design Completion:** Translate the hardware schematic into a compact, dual-layer PCB layout using KiCad, ensuring optimal component placement for the microcontroller, IMU, OLED interface, and haptic motor.
* **Inductive Noise Isolation:** Successfully isolate high-current haptic motor transients from sensitive low-voltage logic lines by employing a dedicated N-channel MOSFET low-side switching network.
* **Signal & Power Integrity:** Implement localized voltage rails ($+3\text{V}3$ and $+5\text{V}$) backed by a continuous bottom copper ground plane (`B.Cu`) to eliminate electromagnetic interference (EMI) and signal return loops.
* **Manufacturability Verification:** Clear all physical board boundary constraints, edge clearances, and track clearance rules within the layout engine to ensure a production-ready design.

### Key Success Metrics
* **Zero DRC Faults:** Achieve a final layout state with **0 errors and 0 warnings** under the KiCad Design Rules Checker (DRC).
* **Electrical Isolation Baseline:** Confirm perfect unpowered circuit safety (cold testing showing infinite resistance between power rails and Ground via a multimeter).
* **Haptic Cue Latency:** Achieve real-world haptic feedback execution within **$\le 50\text{ms}$** of the thigh angle crossing the predefined physical squat depth threshold.
* **Sensor Fusion Accuracy:** Maintain an absolute angle estimation drift of **$< 2^{\circ}$** across a continuous 5-repetition training set compared to video analysis control benchmarks.

